#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:4
msgid "BLAS and LAPACK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:9
msgid "Default behavior for BLAS and LAPACK selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:11
msgid ""
"When a NumPy build is invoked, BLAS and LAPACK library detection happens "
"automatically. The build system will attempt to locate a suitable library, "
"and try a number of known libraries in a certain order - most to least "
"performant. A typical order is: MKL, Accelerate, OpenBLAS, FlexiBLAS, BLIS, "
"plain ``libblas``/``liblapack``. This may vary per platform or over "
"releases. That order, and which libraries are tried, can be changed through "
"the ``blas-order`` and ``lapack-order`` build options, for example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:19
msgid ""
"$ python -m pip install . -Csetup-args=-Dblas-order=openblas,mkl,blis -"
"Csetup-args=-Dlapack-order=openblas,mkl,lapack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:21
msgid ""
"The first suitable library that is found will be used. In case no suitable "
"library is found, the NumPy build will print a warning and then use (slow!) "
"NumPy-internal fallback routines. In order to disallow use of those slow "
"routines, the ``allow-noblas`` build option can be used::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:26
msgid "$ python -m pip install . -Csetup-args=-Dallow-noblas=false"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:28
msgid ""
"By default the LP64 (32-bit integer) interface to BLAS and LAPACK will be "
"used. For building against the ILP64 (64-bit integer) interface, one must "
"use the ``use-ilp64`` build option::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:32
msgid "$ python -m pip install . -Csetup-args=-Duse-ilp64=true"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:38
msgid "Selecting specific BLAS and LAPACK libraries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:40
msgid ""
"The ``blas`` and ``lapack`` build options are set to \"auto\" by default, "
"which means trying all known libraries. If you want to use a specific "
"library, you can set these build options to the library name (typically the "
"lower-case name that ``pkg-config`` expects). For example, to select plain "
"``libblas`` and ``liblapack`` (this is typically Netlib BLAS/LAPACK on Linux "
"distros, and can be dynamically switched between implementations on conda-"
"forge), use::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:47
msgid ""
"$ # for a development build\n"
"$ spin build -C-Dblas=blas -C-Dlapack=lapack\n"
"\n"
"$ # to build and install a wheel\n"
"$ python -m build -Csetup-args=-Dblas=blas -Csetup-args=-Dlapack=lapack\n"
"$ pip install dist/numpy*.whl\n"
"\n"
"$ # Or, with pip>=23.1, this works too:\n"
"$ python -m pip install . -Csetup-args=-Dblas=blas -Csetup-args=-"
"Dlapack=lapack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:57
msgid ""
"Other options that should work (as long as they're installed with ``pkg-"
"config`` support; otherwise they may still be detected but things are "
"inherently more fragile) include ``openblas``, ``mkl``, ``accelerate``, "
"``atlas`` and ``blis``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:64
msgid "Using pkg-config to detect libraries in a nonstandard location"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:66
msgid ""
"The way BLAS and LAPACK detection works under the hood is that Meson tries "
"to discover the specified libraries first with ``pkg-config``, and then with "
"CMake. If all you have is a standalone shared library file (e.g., "
"``armpl_lp64.so`` in ``/a/random/path/lib/`` and a corresponding header file "
"in ``/a/random/path/include/``), then what you have to do is craft your own "
"pkg-config file. It should have a matching name (so in this example, "
"``armpl_lp64.pc``) and may be located anywhere. The ``PKG_CONFIG_PATH`` "
"environment variable should be set to point to the location of the ``.pc`` "
"file. The contents of that file should be::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:76
msgid ""
"libdir=/path/to/library-dir      # e.g., /a/random/path/lib\n"
"includedir=/path/to/include-dir  # e.g., /a/random/path/include\n"
"version=1.2.3                    # set to actual version\n"
"extralib=-lm -lpthread -lgfortran   # if needed, the flags to link in "
"dependencies\n"
"Name: armpl_lp64\n"
"Description: ArmPL - Arm Performance Libraries\n"
"Version: ${version}\n"
"Libs: -L${libdir} -larmpl_lp64      # linker flags\n"
"Libs.private: ${extralib}\n"
"Cflags: -I${includedir}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:87
msgid "To check that this works as expected, you should be able to run::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:89
msgid ""
"$ pkg-config --libs armpl_lp64\n"
"-L/path/to/library-dir -larmpl_lp64\n"
"$ pkg-config --cflags armpl_lp64\n"
"-I/path/to/include-dir"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:96
msgid "Full list of BLAS and LAPACK related build options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:98
msgid ""
"BLAS and LAPACK are complex dependencies. Some libraries have more options "
"that are exposed via build options (see ``meson.options`` in the root of the "
"repo for all of NumPy's build options)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:102
msgid "``blas``: name of the BLAS library to use (default: ``auto``),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:103
msgid "``lapack``: name of the LAPACK library to use (default: ``auto``),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:104
msgid ""
"``allow-noblas``: whether or not to allow building without external BLAS/"
"LAPACK libraries (default: ``true``),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:106
msgid ""
"``blas-order``: order of BLAS libraries to try detecting (default may vary "
"per platform),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:107
msgid "``lapack-order``: order of LAPACK libraries to try detecting,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:108
msgid "``use-ilp64``: whether to use the ILP64 interface (default: ``false``),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:109
msgid ""
"``blas-symbol-suffix``: the symbol suffix to use for the detected libraries "
"(default: ``auto``),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/blas_lapack.rst:110
msgid ""
"``mkl-threading``: which MKL threading layer to use, one of ``seq``, "
"``iomp``, ``gomp``, ``tbb`` (default: ``auto``)."
msgstr ""
